***** Window Event Attributes *****

Events triggered for the window object (applies to the <body> tag):

afterprint    New script Script to be run after the document is printed
beforeprint   New script Script to be run before the document is printed
beforeunload  New script Script to be run before the document is unloaded
error         New script Script to be run when an error occur
haschange     New script Script to be run when the document has changed
load              script Fires after the page is finished loading
message       New script Script to be run when the message is triggered
offline       New script Script to be run when the document goes offline
online        New script Script to be run when the document comes online
pagehide      New script Script to be run when the window is hidden
pageshow      New script Script to be run when the window becomes visible
popstate      New script Script to be run when the window's history changes
redo          New script Script to be run when the document performs a redo
resize        New script Fires when the browser window is resized
storage       New script Script to be run when a Web Storage area is updated
undo          New script Script to be run when the document performs an undo
unload            script Fires once a page has unloaded (or the browser window
                           has been closed)

***** Form Events *****

Events triggered by actions inside a HTML form (applies to almost all HTML
elements, but is most used in form elements):

blur              script Fires the moment that the element loses focus
change            script Fires the moment when the value of the element is
                           changed
contextmenu   New script Script to be run when a context menu is triggered
focus             script Fires the moment when the element gets focus
formchange    New script Script to be run when a form changes
forminput     New script Script to be run when a form gets user input
input         New script Script to be run when an element gets user input
invalid       New script Script to be run when an element is invalid
reset             script Fires when the Reset button in a form is clicked
                           Not supported in HTML5
select            script Fires after some text has been selected in an element
submit            script Fires when a form is submitted

***** Keyboard Events *****

keydown           script Fires when a user is pressing a key
keypress          script Fires when a user presses a key
keyup             script Fires when a user releases a key

***** Mouse Events *****

Events triggered by a mouse, or similar user actions:

click             script Fires on a mouse click on the element
dblclick          script Fires on a mouse double-click on the element
drag          New script Script to be run when an element is dragged
dragend       New script Script to be run at the end of a drag operation
dragenter     New script Script to be run when an element has been dragged to a
                           valid drop target
dragleave     New script Script to be run when an element leaves a valid drop
                           target
dragover      New script Script to be run when an element is being dragged over
                           a valid drop target
dragstart     New script Script to be run at the start of a drag operation
drop          New script Script to be run when dragged element is being dropped
mousedown         script Fires when a mouse button is pressed down on an element
mousemove         script Fires when the mouse pointer moves over an element
mouseout          script Fires when the mouse pointer moves out of an element
mouseover         script Fires when the mouse pointer moves over an element
mouseup           script Fires when a mouse button is released over an element
mousewheel    New script Script to be run when the mouse wheel is being rotated
scroll        New script Script to be run when an element's scrollbar is being
                             scrolled

***** Media Events *****

Events triggered by medias like videos, images and audio (applies to all HTML
elements, but is most common in media elements, like <audio>, <embed>, <img>,
<object>, and <video>):

abort                 script Script to be run on abort
canplay           New script Script to be run when a file is ready to start
                               playing (when it has buffered enough to begin)
canplaythrough    New script Script to be run when a file can be played all
                               the way to the end without pausing for buffering
durationchange    New script Script to be run when the length of the media
                               changes
emptied           New script Script to be run when something bad happens and
                               the file is suddenly unavailable (like
                               unexpectedly disconnects)
ended             New script Script to be run when the media has reach the end
                               (a useful event for messages like &quot;thanks
                               for listening&quot;)
error             New script Script to be run when an error occurs when the
                               file is being loaded
loadeddata        New script Script to be run when media data is loaded
loadedmetadata    New script Script to be run when meta data (like dimensions
                               and duration) are loaded
loadstart         New script Script to be run just as the file begins to load
                               before anything is actually loaded
pause             New script Script to be run when the media is paused either
                               by the user or programmatically
play              New script Script to be run when the media is ready to start
                               playing
playing           New script Script to be run when the media actually has
                               started playing
progress          New script Script to be run when the browser is in the
                               process of getting the media data
ratechange        New script Script to be run each time the playback rate
                               changes (like when a user switches to a slow
                               motion or fast forward mode)
readystatechange  New script Script to be run each time the ready state
                               changes (the ready state tracks the state of the
                               media data)
seeked            New script Script to be run when the seeking attribute is
                               set to false indicating that seeking has ended
seeking           New script Script to be run when the seeking attribute is
                               set to true indicating that seeking is active
stalled           New script Script to be run when the browser is unable to
                               fetch the media data for whatever reason
suspend           New script Script to be run when fetching the media data is
                               stopped before it is completely loaded for
                               whatever reason
timeupdate        New script Script to be run when the playing position has
                               changed (like when the user fast forwards to a
                               different point in the media)
volumechange      New script Script to be run each time the volume is changed
                               which (includes setting the volume to
                               &quot;mute&quot;)
waiting           New script Script to be run when the media has paused but is
                               expected to resume (like when the media pauses to
                               buffer more data)
